## Purchase Order

A Purchase Order represents a user's intent to purchase one or more lottery tickets.

The Purchase Order exists before payment is initiated.

Each Purchase Order contains:

- unique order identifier;
- purchaser identifier;
- selected lottery draw;
- ticket quantity;
- ticket price;
- total amount;
- currency;
- creation timestamp;
- current status.

Possible statuses:

- Created
- Payment Pending
- Paid
- Failed
- Expired
- Refunded
- Cancelled

Orders cannot be modified after successful payment.

---

## Payment Processing

Payments are processed only through supported external payment providers.

The platform never processes or stores payment card information.

Each payment is linked to exactly one Purchase Order.

Possible payment states:

- Pending
- Authorized
- Confirmed
- Failed
- Cancelled
- Refunded

Only the **Confirmed** status allows ticket generation.

---

## Payment Confirmation

A payment is considered successful only after receiving official confirmation from the payment provider.

Client-side success messages are never treated as proof of payment.

All financial operations begin only after server-side confirmation.

Duplicate confirmations must not create duplicate tickets or duplicate financial records.

The payment confirmation process must be fully idempotent.

---

## Ticket Generation

Tickets are generated only after payment confirmation.

The system creates the exact number of tickets specified in the Purchase Order.

Every ticket receives:

- unique ticket identifier;
- draw identifier;
- owner identifier;
- purchase timestamp;
- annual draw eligibility;
- weekly draw eligibility.

Ticket generation is atomic.

Either all tickets are successfully created or none are created.

---

# Revenue Allocation

Immediately after successful ticket generation, the payment amount is automatically distributed.

The allocation is performed entirely by the system.

No administrator can modify allocation percentages.

For every confirmed payment:

- 70% is allocated to the Weekly Jackpot;
- 20% is allocated as Company Revenue;
- 10% is allocated to the Annual Jackpot.

Each allocation creates independent immutable ledger records.

---

## Weekly Jackpot Allocation

Every confirmed payment contributes exactly seventy percent of its value to the Weekly Jackpot associated with the selected draw.

The allocation becomes permanent immediately after payment confirmation.

Weekly Jackpot values are calculated from ledger records.

The jackpot amount is never manually entered.

---

## Annual Jackpot Allocation

Every confirmed payment contributes ten percent of its value to the current Annual Jackpot.

Every confirmed ticket automatically becomes eligible for the Annual Draw.

No additional purchase is required.

The Annual Jackpot is calculated exclusively from ledger records.

---

## Company Revenue Allocation

Twenty percent of every confirmed payment is allocated to Company Revenue.

Revenue allocation is immutable.

Revenue records are included in financial reporting and audit logs.

---

# Financial Ledger

The Financial Ledger is the single source of truth for all financial operations performed within Amazing Chance.

Every financial event creates one or more immutable ledger entries.

Ledger records can never be modified or deleted.

If a correction is required, the system creates additional compensating records.

The original record always remains unchanged.

The ledger contains:

- payments;
- jackpot allocations;
- company revenue allocations;
- prize payments;
- refunds;
- system financial events.

All balances, reports and financial statistics are calculated from ledger records.

