# Functional Requirements

## FR-001 Purchase Order Creation

The system shall create a unique Purchase Order before initiating payment.

Each Purchase Order shall include:

- unique identifier;
- user identifier;
- draw identifier;
- ticket quantity;
- ticket price;
- total payment amount;
- currency;
- creation timestamp;
- order status.

---

## FR-002 External Payment Processing

The system shall process payments only through approved external payment providers.

The platform shall never process or store payment card data.

---

## FR-003 Payment Verification

The system shall verify every payment using server-to-server confirmation received from the payment provider.

Client-side confirmations shall never be considered valid proof of payment.

---

## FR-004 Ticket Generation

The system shall generate lottery tickets only after successful payment confirmation.

No ticket may exist without a confirmed payment.

---

## FR-005 Automatic Revenue Allocation

After payment confirmation, the system shall automatically allocate payment funds:

- 70% → Weekly Jackpot;
- 20% → Company Revenue;
- 10% → Annual Jackpot.

The allocation shall occur automatically without administrator intervention.

---

## FR-006 Immutable Ledger

Every financial operation shall create immutable ledger entries.

Ledger records shall never be modified or deleted.

---

## FR-007 Annual Draw Eligibility

Every confirmed ticket shall automatically participate in the Annual Draw.

No additional purchase or registration shall be required.

---

## FR-008 Weekly Draw Eligibility

Every confirmed ticket shall participate only in the Weekly Draw for which it was purchased.

---

## FR-009 Financial Audit

Every financial operation shall be fully traceable.

Audit records shall include:

- timestamp;
- event type;
- entity identifier;
- initiating component;
- operation result.

---

## FR-010 Prize Payments

Prize payments shall create new immutable ledger entries.

Prize payments shall never modify previous financial records.

---

## FR-011 Refund Processing

Refunds shall create compensating ledger entries.

Original payment records shall remain unchanged.

---

## FR-012 Idempotency

Repeated payment confirmations shall never create:

- duplicate tickets;
- duplicate ledger entries;
- duplicate allocations;
- duplicate prizes.

---

## FR-013 Financial Reporting

All financial reports shall be generated exclusively from ledger records.

No report shall rely on manually maintained balances.

---

## FR-014 Historical Integrity

The system shall preserve the complete financial history for every Purchase Order.

Historical records shall remain accessible for audit purposes.

---

## FR-015 Financial Consistency

All financial operations shall be executed atomically.

If any step fails, the entire transaction shall be rolled back.

