# Security Requirements

## SEC-001 Immutable Financial Records

Financial ledger records shall be immutable.

Modification and deletion of existing ledger records are prohibited.

---

## SEC-002 Payment Verification

Only server-to-server payment confirmations received from approved payment providers shall be accepted.

Client-side confirmations shall never initiate financial operations.

---

## SEC-003 Financial Authorization

Every financial operation shall be executed only by authorized system components.

Direct user access to financial processing is prohibited.

---

## SEC-004 Administrator Restrictions

Administrators shall not be able to:

- modify ledger records;
- modify payment records;
- modify jackpot allocations;
- modify company revenue allocations;
- modify prize allocations;
- modify ticket ownership;
- modify draw eligibility.

---

## SEC-005 Complete Audit Trail

Every financial event shall generate an audit record.

Audit records shall include:

- timestamp;
- event type;
- entity identifier;
- initiating component;
- execution result.

Audit records shall be immutable.

---

## SEC-006 Allocation Integrity

Revenue allocation percentages shall be fixed within the system configuration.

Financial allocations shall not be editable through the administration interface.

---

## SEC-007 Atomic Financial Operations

Financial operations shall execute as atomic transactions.

Partial execution is prohibited.

---

## SEC-008 Duplicate Protection

Repeated payment confirmations shall never create duplicate:

- tickets;
- allocations;
- ledger entries;
- prize payments.

---

## SEC-009 Financial Consistency

The system shall guarantee financial consistency under concurrent requests.

---

## SEC-010 Data Integrity

Every ledger record shall reference the originating business entity whenever applicable.

Broken financial references shall not be permitted.

---

# Validation Rules

## VAL-001

A Purchase Order must exist before payment.

---

## VAL-002

A payment cannot be confirmed more than once.

---

## VAL-003

Tickets may only be generated after successful payment confirmation.

---

## VAL-004

Every confirmed payment shall generate exactly one allocation event.

---

## VAL-005

The allocation percentages must always equal:

- Weekly Jackpot — 70%;
- Company Revenue — 20%;
- Annual Jackpot — 10%.

Total allocation must equal 100%.

---

## VAL-006

Every generated ticket must reference an existing Purchase Order.

---

## VAL-007

Every generated ticket must reference an existing Draw.

---

## VAL-008

Every confirmed ticket must automatically receive Annual Draw eligibility.

---

## VAL-009

Each ledger record shall contain a valid timestamp.

---

## VAL-010

Each ledger record shall contain a valid financial amount.

Negative allocation values are prohibited unless generated by an approved compensating transaction.

---

# Error States

## ERR-001 Payment Failed

Payment provider rejected the transaction.

No tickets are generated.

---

## ERR-002 Payment Timeout

Payment confirmation was not received within the allowed time.

Order status becomes Expired.

---

## ERR-003 Duplicate Confirmation

A repeated payment confirmation was received.

The system ignores the duplicate request.

---

## ERR-004 Allocation Failure

Revenue allocation could not be completed.

The financial transaction is rolled back.

---

## ERR-005 Ticket Generation Failure

Ticket creation failed.

The entire financial transaction is rolled back.

---

## ERR-006 Ledger Write Failure

The system failed to write immutable ledger records.

The transaction is cancelled.

---

## ERR-007 Invalid Allocation

Calculated allocation percentages do not equal 100%.

The transaction is rejected.

---

## ERR-008 Invalid Draw Reference

The Purchase Order references a non-existent or unavailable Draw.

Ticket generation is rejected.

---

## ERR-009 Financial Consistency Error

Ledger validation detects inconsistent financial data.

The transaction is suspended for investigation.

---

## ERR-010 Audit Failure

Audit information could not be recorded.

The financial transaction shall not be completed until audit logging succeeds.

