# Acceptance Criteria

The Financial System shall be considered complete when:

- Purchase Orders are created before payment.
- Payments are confirmed only by external payment providers.
- Tickets are generated only after successful payment confirmation.
- Every confirmed payment is automatically allocated:
  - 70% Weekly Jackpot
  - 20% Company Revenue
  - 10% Annual Jackpot
- Every confirmed ticket is automatically eligible for:
  - Weekly Draw
  - Annual Draw
- Every financial operation creates immutable ledger records.
- Administrators cannot modify financial data.
- Financial reports are generated exclusively from ledger records.
- Complete audit history is preserved.
- All financial operations are atomic and traceable.

